#    This script gather data from Yahoo Weather API and transform it into 
#    a home made database text file called weather_db2.txt
#    More info from Yahoo Weather API can be found at:
#    http://developer.yahoo.com/weather/
#
#    This file stores weather data regarding Cities, every city is separated 
#    with a "|" symbol. Every single data regarding a city is separated 
#    with a ";" This gives as a structure like:
#                        City 1      City 2     City 3
#                     -;-;-;-;-;-|-;-;-;-;-;-|-;-;-;-;-;-|
#                     -;-;-;-;-;-|-;-;-;-;-;-|-;-;-;-;-;-|
#                     -;-;-;-;-;-|-;-;-;-;-;-|-;-;-;-;-;-|
#
#    From this db we generate the json data weather_json.js
#    And index.html finish the job by using jquery, jquery.flot.js 
#    and prototype.js to draw the charts.
#    More info from this librarys can be found at:
#    http://code.google.com/p/flot/
#    http://www.prototypejs.org/

